# Testing Standards

Use Vitest and Testing Library for tests.

- Prefer user-visible assertions: roles, labels, text, and accessible names.
- Do not test HeroUI internals. Test MuseHub composition, contracts, and user flows.
- Add tests for new route-level pages, complex features, filtering/sorting logic, data transformations, and regression fixes.
- Keep smoke tests small. Use focused unit tests for pure model or contract logic.
- Put test setup in `src/test/setup.ts`.
- Run `npm run test` before finishing feature or refactor work.

Default commands:

```bash
npm run lint
npm run test
npm run build
```
